<TITLE> RMG industry fetched over $96b in 20 years </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 27 (bdnews24.com)The readymade garment industry earned $ 96,308.92 million in foreign currency in the 20 years from 1990-91 until 2009-2010. Of this, Tk 760,612.25 million came from apparels exports from Jan-Nov, 2009, said commerce minister Faruk Khan on Wednesday in parliament, answering questions. In reply to another query he told parliament that the government will soon fix the amount of allowed inventory of essential commodities and also for how long they will be allowed to retain the inventories, in an apparent bid to prevent hoarding. Replying to queries of Mushtaque Ahmed Ruhi, MP of Netrakona-1, Khan said the government would take those measures in implementing a Competition Act. He said, "Work is underway to implement an act (Competition Act) for fixing the storage and duration of storage of essential commodities." Answering to another query by Khulna-4 MP Molla Jalaluddin, the minister said, "Prices of some essentials and food products are rising suddenly because of manipulation and collusion of businessmen." He said that the government was fully aware of the phenomenon. "Already some businessmen have been marked." b
